description:
&lt;p&gt;Great Ormond Street Hospital (GOSH) is a globally renowned children’s hospital, championing innovation across more than 60 clinical specialties and providing ground-breaking treatments for the rarest and most complex conditions to sick children at home and abroad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are based in central London close to Oxford Circus, Convent Garden, Leicester Square and St Pancras International for Eurostar and travel to Europe so you’ll be at the heart of the action as you take your skills to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Bank worker, your work will help ensure that we are making a difference to the lives of the children that we care for and support our colleagues who are at the front line of providing their care. You may have seen the hospital featured on ITV’s &lt;strong&gt;Paul O’Grady’s Little Heroes&lt;/strong&gt; which provided a unique insight into the lives of the brave and resilient children who are treated here every day. Use the links on right to watch a couple of episodes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our bank workers are valuable to the workforce at GOSH and equally enjoy the same benefits as staff at Great Ormond Street Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With any Audiology related questions, please email Samantha.Burton@gosh.nhs.uk and I can pass the query onto the department.&lt;/p&gt;
